  <title>Clutter.Text::insert-text</title>
<synopsis><code mime="text/x-python">
def callback(text, new_text, new_text_length, position, user_param1, ...)
</code></synopsis>
<p>This signal is emitted when text is inserted into the actor by
the user. It is emitted before @self text changes.</p>

<table>
<tr>
<td><p>text :</p></td>
<td><p>instance of Clutter.Text that is emitting the signal</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>new_text :</p></td>
<td><p>the new text to insert</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>new_text_length :</p></td>
<td><p>the length of the new text, in bytes, or -1 if new_text is nul-terminated</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>position :</p></td>
<td><p>the position, in characters, at which to insert the new text. this is an in-out parameter.  After the signal emission is finished, it should point after the newly inserted text.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>user_param1 :</p></td>
<td><p>first user parameter (if any) specified with the connect() method</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>... :</p></td>
<td><p>additional user parameters (if any)</p></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Since 1.2</p>
</page>
